    {
      "id": "70f7755b-744c-452c-aaf5-32b8bdde1640",
      "text": "## Introduction",
      "segment_type": "section",
      "level": 0,
      "title": null,
      "parent_id": null,
      "children_ids": [
        "c8ae2e12-5e5a-4ad3-914b-cafac841fd8b"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "position": {
          "start": 46,
          "end": 62
        }
      },
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "c8ae2e12-5e5a-4ad3-914b-cafac841fd8b",
          "text": "Knowledge graphs represent a powerful way to organize and interconnect information, providing a structured representation of knowledge that combines the flexibility of graphs with the expressiveness of semantics. They are essential tools in modern information systems, enabling advanced data integration, reasoning, and discovery.",
          "segment_type": "paragraph",
          "level": 1,
          "title": null,
          "parent_id": "70f7755b-744c-452c-aaf5-32b8bdde1640",
          "children_ids": [],
          "metadata": {
            "position": {
              "start": 63,
              "end": 360
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "c41f28fa-c508-4b15-93eb-e09fa02c57af",
      "text": "## Core Components",
      "segment_type": "section",
      "level": 0,
      "title": null,
      "parent_id": null,
      "children_ids": [
        "d81851f0-71ec-4d59-9f9e-293ab335a3f3",
        "7592abaa-d940-4c19-b8e0-5c70034ca371"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "position": {
          "start": 361,
          "end": 380
        }
      },
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "d81851f0-71ec-4d59-9f9e-293ab335a3f3",
          "text": "The fundamental building blocks of knowledge graphs include:",
          "segment_type": "paragraph",
          "level": 1,
          "title": null,
          "parent_id": "c41f28fa-c508-4b15-93eb-e09fa02c57af",
          "children_ids": [],
          "metadata": {
            "position": {
              "start": 381,
              "end": 442
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "7592abaa-d940-4c19-b8e0-5c70034ca371",
          "text": "1. **Entities** - Representing real-world objects, concepts, or events (nodes in the graph)\n2. **Relationships** - Expressing how entities are connected to each other (edges)\n3. **Attributes** - Properties that describe entities and relationships in more detail\n4. **Ontologies** - Formal specifications of conceptualizations that define entity types and relationship semantics",
          "segment_type": "list",
          "level": 1,
          "title": null,
          "parent_id": "c41f28fa-c508-4b15-93eb-e09fa02c57af",
          "children_ids": [],
          "metadata": {
            "position": {
              "start": 443,
              "end": 771
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "da41d42c-c7c8-4c26-8877-ba8d5d8ddedd",
      "text": "## Applications",
      "segment_type": "section",
      "level": 0,
      "title": null,
      "parent_id": null,
      "children_ids": [
        "ebb56a4e-87c1-4b82-b09c-33f3b94a5e8f",
        "1212951a-6f8c-4e9a-b6e3-23f9cf2b0fe4"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "position": {
          "start": 772,
          "end": 788
        }
      },
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "ebb56a4e-87c1-4b82-b09c-33f3b94a5e8f",
          "text": "Knowledge graphs find applications across numerous domains:",
          "segment_type": "paragraph",
          "level": 1,
          "title": null,
          "parent_id": "da41d42c-c7c8-4c26-8877-ba8d5d8ddedd",
          "children_ids": [],
          "metadata": {
            "position": {
              "start": 789,
              "end": 847
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "1212951a-6f8c-4e9a-b6e3-23f9cf2b0fe4",
          "text": "- **Search engines** use them to understand query semantics and enhance results with structured information\n- **Recommendation systems** leverage knowledge graphs to model complex user preferences and item relationships\n- **Scientific research** employs them to integrate heterogeneous data sources and discover new connections\n- **Enterprise information systems** utilize knowledge graphs to create unified views of organizational knowledge",
          "segment_type": "list",
          "level": 1,
          "title": null,
          "parent_id": "da41d42c-c7c8-4c26-8877-ba8d5d8ddedd",
          "children_ids": [],
          "metadata": {
            "position": {
              "start": 848,
              "end": 1259
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}